00323 /**
00324  * cvmx_led_en
00325  *
00326  * LED_EN = LED Interface Enable
00327  *
00328  *
00329  * Notes:
00330  * The LED interface is comprised of a shift chain with a parallel latch.  LED
00331  * data is shifted out on each fallingg edge of led_clk and then captured by
00332  * led_lat.
00333  *
00334  * The LED shift chain is comprised of the following...
00335  *
00336  *      32  - UDD header
00337  *      6x8 - per port status
00338  *      17  - debug port
00339  *      32  - UDD trailer
00340  *
00341  * for a total of 129 bits.
00342  *
00343  * UDD header is programmable from 0-32 bits (LED_UDD_CNT0) and will shift out
00344  * LSB to MSB (LED_UDD_DAT0[0], LED_UDD_DAT0[1],
00345  * ... LED_UDD_DAT0[LED_UDD_CNT0].
00346  *
00347  * The per port status is also variable.  Systems can control which ports send
00348  * data (LED_PRT) as well as the status content (LED_PRT_FMT and
00349  * LED_PRT_STATUS*).  When multiple ports are enabled, they come out in lowest
00350  * port to highest port (prt0, prt1, ...).
00351  *
00352  * The debug port data can also be added to the LED chain (LED_DBG).  When
00353  * enabled, the debug data shifts out LSB to MSB.
00354  *
00355  * The UDD trailer data is identical to the header data, but uses LED_UDD_CNT1
00356  * and LED_UDD_DAT1.
00357  */
00358 union cvmx_led_en {
00359     uint64_t u64;
00360     struct cvmx_led_en_s {
00361 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
00362     uint64_t reserved_1_63                : 63;
00363     uint64_t en                           : 1;  /**< Enable the LED interface shift-chain */
00364 #else
00365     uint64_t en                           : 1;
00366     uint64_t reserved_1_63                : 63;
00367 #endif
00368     } s;
00369     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn38xx;
00370     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn38xxp2;
00371     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn56xx;
00372     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn56xxp1;
00373     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn58xx;
00374     struct cvmx_led_en_s                  cn58xxp1;
00375 };
00376 typedef union cvmx_led_en cvmx_led_en_t;

00441 /**
00442  * cvmx_led_prt_fmt
00443  *
00444  * LED_PRT_FMT = LED Port Status Infomation Format
00445  *
00446  *
00447  * Notes:
00448  * TX: RGMII TX block is sending packet data or extends on the port
00449  * RX: RGMII RX block has received non-idle cycle
00450  *
00451  * For short transfers, LEDs will remain on for at least one blink cycle
00452  */
00453 union cvmx_led_prt_fmt {
00454     uint64_t u64;
00455     struct cvmx_led_prt_fmt_s {
00456 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
00457     uint64_t reserved_4_63                : 60;
00458     uint64_t format                       : 4;  /**< Port Status Information for each enabled port in
00459                                                          LED_PRT.  The formats are below
00460                                                          0x0: [ LED_PRT_STATUS[0]            ]
00461                                                          0x1: [ LED_PRT_STATUS[1:0]          ]
00462                                                          0x2: [ LED_PRT_STATUS[3:0]          ]
00463                                                          0x3: [ LED_PRT_STATUS[5:0]          ]
00464                                                          0x4: [ (RX|TX), LED_PRT_STATUS[0]   ]
00465                                                          0x5: [ (RX|TX), LED_PRT_STATUS[1:0] ]
